name: 03- Retail Analysis
content:
Store/Retail Analysis


Total Sales by Store

This visualization displays the total sales for all stores individually:

Key Findings:

  • N2 dominates with ~$600 in sales
  • N3 and N4 show moderate sales (~$250-275)
  • N5 and N1 perform lowest, with N1 at ~$100

Total sales per store

This graph shows the total sales performance for store all stores:

Key Findings:

  • Highest sales peak on day 3, reaching nearly $200,000, followed by high sales on days 25 and 30
  • Most days maintain sales between $50,000-$100,000
  • Store N2 (green) and N4 (yellow) frequently show the largest contributions to total sales


Average Sales per store

This graph shows the average sales performance for store all stores:

Key Findings:

  • Major sales spikes on days 22 and 31, reaching ~$3,000, mainly from N2
  • Regular days average $500-$1,500 across stores
  • Store N2 (green) consistently shows the highest sales contribution throughout the month



Number of Units Sold by Top 10 Categories

This column chart displays unit sales volume across product categories:

Key Findings:

  • Biscuits lead with approximately 4K units sold
  • Chocolate follows with about 1K units
  • Salty snacks rank third with roughly 1K units
  • There's a sharp decline after the top 3 categories

Sales From Top 10 Categories

This visualization shows sales value performance by category:

Key Findings:

  • Biscuit dominates with sales of approximately 5.6L worth of sales.
  • Packaged tea rank second with about 1.8L in sales.
  • A gradual decline is observed across categories.
  • Lowest performing categories (Butter Margr) show minimal sales value.


Total Sales by Week Analysis

This visualization shows weekly sales performance:

Key Findings:

  • Week 4 shows highest performance with ~950,000 in sales
  • Week 1 follows closely with ~870,000 in sales
  • Weeks 2 and 3 show lower performance (~600,000 and ~530,000 respectively)


10 Most Expensive Categories Analysis

This visualization shows price distribution across top categories:

Key Findings:

  • Olive oils lead significantly with ~$540 average price
  • Packaged category ranks second at ~$240
  • Gradual price decline observed across categories
  • Fragran category shows lowest pricing among top 10 at ~$170


10 Least Expensive Categories - Price Analysis

This visualization shows average prices across different product categories:

Key Findings:

  • Hair care products (Conditioner and Dyes) are the most expensive items, averaging around $51-52
  • Cleaning products sit at the bottom of the price range at approximately $30, creating a notable price gap from top categories


Quantity of Items Sold by Store Analysis

This visualization shows unit sales across different store locations:

Key Findings:

  • Store N4 leads in sales volume with approximately 30 units sold
  • There's a significant drop to the lowest performer (N3) which sold only about 15 units, half of N4's volume


Total Sales by Month Analysis

This visualization shows sales performance across three months:

Key Findings:

  • Month 3 (M3) achieved the highest sales at approximately 1.04 million
  • There's a steady declining trend from M3 to M1, with M1 recording about 935,000 in sales
